Different text types and the ways of teaching them on first and second school stages. The difference between oral and written text. Compiling and analysing texts.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give students a comprehensive overview of teaching oral and written communication, combining theoretical knowledge with methodology for teaching Estonian on first and second school stages.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course students will know different text types and can teach students to compile them; know the main parts of oral presentation and written text; can write different texts; will use age-appropriate vocabulary in teaching.
